<rate>1</rate><Review>Unfortunately, I can't recommend this winery. To be fair it wasn't based on their wine, but their lack of customer service and poor representation.

The same gentlemen that told me 5 days ago that we didnt need a reservation told me today, (after our 30 minute uber ride) that he had to be pick up something and would be there  1 hour after his posted hours because we didnt make a reservations.

I was able to validate that he was the same gentlemen who told me I didnt need a reservation and he even recalled our conversation details.

I then asked where we could go for an hour to try an work with him since we invested so much time to get to Laguna Canyon Winery.  He said you can go to the car shop, then said you can walk down the canyon to the the beach (no walking path and dangerous turns) or you can try a different. He apologized and said there was nothing he could do.

Please save yourself a trip, this winery stands alone  by itself in between auto collision and car repair shops. It's a shame that we didn't get to try the wines. I can't recommend this winery as there was no care or concern for their customers, you can't rely on their posted hours and this is a stand alone winery with no other choices.

We told our next Uber driver about our horrible experience at Laguna Canyon Winery and he apologized for the poor treatment and suggested we visit Mozambique.

The food, wine and service are amazing and the views are spectacular. Highly recommend Mozambique!!!!

Sincere, Michele< /Review><pictures>None</pictures>< resp>

<rating>5< /rating>< Text>
I was a little bit hesitant on coming because I really wanted to go out on an outside vineyard tour with the actual grapes in line in a garden but the owner is very personable and you can tell he is doing exactly what he loves. Wine is his passion.. the way he speaks and experience, he has had over more than 2 decades in the industry. He explained how he got into it and a few other locations he has wineries in as well as previous positions he worked in that he didn‚Äôt  like before getting into this business. A definite recommend. I am from NY and was just in the town but i do plan on visiting California more often and will definitely come back. The wines were great- never had a better merlot, and he has an option for whites and reds that are filtered and unfiltered. I really thought  it was cool that he had machines and a card system keeping track of the balance we can use and dispensing the wines for us at the same time.</Text>

<rate>5</rate>< text>
My husband and I attended a 1st Friday of the Month Wine Tasting Party that included a variety of appetizers, a super filling buffet, music and amazing wines! MANY of their wines are delicious and I'm so happy I have a new fave winery less than 30 minutes from my home.

I tend to be more of a red wine fan and I loved their 7 Barrel, Petite Verdot and Purple Paws. I was also pleasantly surprised to learn they have a raspberry sparkling. It will be a perfect addition to our holiday meals!

For $40, it was a great value, especially since we got 10 wine tasting on top of all the delicious foods. They even ended our meal with chocolate dipped cookies!!

I'd highly recommend for a girls night or date night.<//text>

< text>
On the first Friday of the month, I had the distinct pleasure of attending a Wine Tasting Event at Laguna Canyon Winery.

As I walked in the doors I was greeted by one of the owners and several staff members. I was immediately made to feel welcome and really liked the feel of the place.

We enjoyed several red wines, white wines, dessert wines and more. My favorites were the 7 Barrel, Petite-Sirah and the Tawny Port. All in all the Friday night tasting includes ten - 1 ounce flights.  In addition to this there is live music and delicious food. I highly recommend Laguna Canyon Winery.<//text>

<user_name>Pete Shieh< /user_name>< user_id>
112923256788955138104< /user_id>
<date>1476221961891<//date><pictures>None<//pictures>< rating>
5<//rating>
<Gmap_id>0x80dce5d09f1b5f8d:0x5ba5cc4c42d40f93< /Gmap_id>< resp>
None< /resp>
< Review>
Came here past Friday night with a group of food and wine enthusiasts (EatNDrinkGeeks), for their 1st Friday of the Month Wine Tasting party from 6-9pm every month. Well, maybe not every month, but check the events calendar from their website.

It was surprisingly packed.  Outside parking was difficult to find as they share a lot with what looks like a car repair shop. Once inside, you can get 10 tastings of 1 ounce pours  and appetizers and hot food with no place to put your food. But you know what? I loved it here because the people here were super nice and Marlowe is super passionate about his award winning wines.  They've won numerous awards from the OC Fair.

They were serving whites on left side and reds on the side closer to the street. I am more particular to the Reds here because I love my Cabs. So I was able to taste their '12 Cab, the 4 blend, 5 blend, 7 blend, the syrah, and the cab syrah.  Taste wise, I personally like big, bold fruity flavors with some oak but not too overpowering. So without going into too much detail and sounding like a wine snob, I liked the 7 blend and the 4 blend the best here. It's like tasting an Anejo and a Reposado if this was tequila as the 7 was a bit smoother and the 4 was a bit younger but you can taste all the profiles.

The people behind the counter were super nice and hilarious. I got to meet Leann and Denise as they were pouring the white wines. Their Russian River Canyon Cuvee is quite nice, slightly dry, not sweet, and great on the nose with punch of fruit. Super easy to drink, probably best now.

They do all the blending in house I believe. There was a sign right above the entrance way stating they bring grapes from all over the place into here. The barrels inside the tasting room are real with wine fermenting away.  They do have a small water dispenser, which is my only gripe here. Definitely not big enough!

If you buy a wine during the event, you get to keep the etched glass.  Background wise, there was live music from Saeed Marandi. It was a fun time with fellow friends over wine. This place is definitely worth checking out when you're in the area like for SawDust down the street.< /Review>
</record>

Nice flowers. Terrible service.

I had made 2 separate online orders of 3 floral stands for my aunt‚Äôs funeral - so 6 in total. I received an email saying that the first order could not be processed due to an issue with the credit card info so I called in immediately to resolve it. While it took a couple tries to run it through, the woman on the other line assured me that the payment went through and everything was all good. On the day of delivery only 4 had arrived out of the 6. I called the shop to see what had happened and the person whom I spoke to said that I only received 4 flowers because that‚Äôs what I paid for, but I kept responding that I had actually ordered 6. Apparently for some reason, when I had called to fix the card issue, the person who helped me only charged for 1/3 flowers in the first order. Then the person on the phone accused me of incorrectly stating my order. They kept saying I sent in four separate orders each with different order numbers, but I was looking at my purchase history on their site and it showed only 2 orders, each with 3 floral arrangements. <Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
You need to visit Wild Oak.
They have so much to offer. No place like it.

They make their own Tie-Dye shirts and other clothing in house.
The collection of incense is mind boggling.
Plus so many items you will find no where else.

Every time I visit, it is all the great memories from the seventies flooding in, and creation of new memories.

I wish there were more stars to give.

This is a family owned business of over 25 years.

The owners are the most honest people you would ever hope to meet.

Do something for yourself and feel good for awhile and visit The Wild Oak.

Easy to find. Right across the street from the old State Theater on Oak street.

Thank you,

I hate to write this part. These are my opinions and observations.
Investigate for yourself. You will be glad you did.

Also:
Please don't tailgate
Use turn signals
Stay off phone.

Love life üòò< /review>

I don't normally shop at Walmart except for a few items like Coolwater Cologne. This huge bottle pictured I believe cost a little over $50.

I recently bought a Dodge ram with a diesel motor in it in Louisiana and drove it back to Southern Cali.

The original owner gave me the service records and in that was the Walmart receipt for the 2 huge batteries the truck uses.

It was just under 3 years from date of purchase which was at a Walmart in Florida. So the invoice had someone else's name on it,  Louisiana address with a receipt from FL.

I had to argue with them a little too get them to re test the batteries because they used a handheld load tester... after removing the batteries and testing them on a bigger load tester they confirmed the batteries were toast.

They took my paperwork and got new batteries in my truck and didn't question anything on the paperwork. It says right in the invoice that the warranty is non transferable.

Anyways that's my experience with Walmart.

Hope this helps!< /Review>

First time here. 3 Wal-marts in one day looking for a few dining canopies. None of them had the $49 special so I ended up buying two $79 canopies. I'm happy with the purchase as they are better quality and white as opposed to blue so they should reflect more heat. They are also vented at the top to help prevent toppling in high winds. There were three customers in line ahead of us and it took 25 minutes to give them money.</Review>

<user>106049061616897013134</user><Response>None< /Response><user_name>LM 9999< /user_name><GmapID>0x80dc75b26992381f:0xee60197de9274d9c<//GmapID>< time>

<pictures>None< /pictures>< Review>
FIVE STARS  Vista WALMART! In the last two months,  I have made quick grocery store to home trips. Betw.the Oceanside stores and Encin Walmarts, I have poured down the sink at least $140 of ordinary traditional milk with  exp dates of 14 to 18 days away.  Most likely milk  got stuck for hours in non-refrigerated areas during transport to store or prior to being put in the Walmart dairy walkin-refrigerator.  I repeatedly tried Pickup--Service. No matter what time of pickup,  these other Wlm were out of ordinary milk and no substitutions. (I also would go in--no milk, too.)
THANK YOU VISTA WALMART.  I have always been able to come in real quick and find ordinary milk in half gallons and quarts. Each time properly refrigerated, too.  This has been a problem with V grocery chain, too, at certain locations. No, I did not go back each time with my receipt and empty milk jugs.  Its been many weeks,  I have only been able to leave the house  no more than 2-3 times a week for groc or pharmacy only. Thus, I have enjoyed the feeling of driving outside and my short walks in the store. THANK YOU VISTA DEPT. DAIRY PEOPLE--Each of you--at different levels. The refrigerator shelves are clean. Glass doors clean. The milk is properly stocked and rotated. I purchased product I could rely on. Thank You.< /Review>

< Review>
This order was placed online.  Total for the items was initially ~$29.  The order wasn't allowed because it was < $30.  After doubling some items, the order was accepted.

Default for online orders is store pickup.  Order was changed to deliver.  Pickup orders have no added cost.  Delivery orders of $49 get a ~$7.90 charge.

Pickup was available same day. Delivery was available next day or any day of the week.

Placing the order is simple find and click process.  One click gets a quantity of one. I didn't try two clicks.

When the order is created clicking the quantity number increments the quantity up or down.

Order pickup happens at the Pickup Door.  There special parking spaces with signs that point the way.

To know when the order is ready, they send a text with a reply link.  Clicking the link will open the Walmart App so you can let them know you are on the way.

I don't have their App so showed up at the planned time space.  A man came out and asked my name.  He then went back in and return 10 minutes later with the order.

This approach can keep the shopping time to 30 minutes in my case.<//Review>

You never really appreciate a Walmart Supercenter until you have taken a British family in the middle of the night.

The sheer amazement they displayed just illuminated how jaded we are, taking for granted the ability to get whatever you want, whenever you want.

< review>
Their AUTO CENTER is a NIGHTMARE!!!
Gabe, the manger, appeared SNOTTY when I stopped him from letting more air out of my 44 PSI inflated tires (he told me all about how he couldn't and I shouldn't over-inflate (my 44 PSI rated) tires...the "new guy" came out from the pit and I asked him..."how many grease zerks did you find"???...he told me, my vehicle doesn't have any, after I explained to him that a grease zerk is that fitting you connect to the grease gun...the old white guy was my next choice...he already knew I have about 4 zerks under there and he took the new guy down again to show him where they are...meanwhile I was inside telling Gabe, I would be telling some people about this neglect, LIE and cover-up by Gabe himself!!!
Why bother commenting???
